        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Terrorist Asset Seizure Reform Act of 2018 </b></p> <p>This bill requires a financial institution to transfer to the Department of the Treasury (1)&nbsp;interest paid&nbsp;on certain bank accounts that are frozen as a result of sanctions; and (2)&nbsp;after&nbsp;providing notice and an opportunity for the owner to challenge,&nbsp;frozen or otherwise blocked assets affiliated with specified terrorist activity.&nbsp;Assets and interest confiscated under the bill must be deposited into a fund made available to the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) for grants related to terrorism prevention.</p>]]></text>
